<TEXT>
jordan has reached an agreement with 
britain to buy an undisclosed number of the multirole tornado 
fighter jets jordans official news agency petra reported 
a senior air force official told the associated press on monday 
that the agreement was formalized during a meeting between king 
hussein and prime minister margaret thatcher of britain 
he did not say when the meeting took place but hussein has been 
in britain for several days on a private visit 
the official who requested anonymity in line with air force 
regulations refused to say what the deal was worth or how many 
planes were involved petra also did not give such details 
sources said earlier the king was seeking to buy 40 tornado 
warplanes 
the agency said the deal was part of the the kings desire to 
develop and strengthen the defense capabilities of the jordanian 
air force 
jordan turned to britain and france after the us congress 
blocked a deal involving the sale of f20 and f16 warplanes to the 
jordanian air force 
last year saudi arabia bought 72 tornado jets from britain for 
similar reasons in february france agreed to sell jordan 20 
mirage 2000 fighter jets 
