<TEXT>
protesters stoned the motorcade of 
president augusto pinochet sunday during a campaign tour on the 
15th anniversary of the military coup he led that ousted the 
government of marxist president salvador allende 
in the coastal resort of vina del mar thousands of leftists 
battled riot police following a memorial service at the grave of 
allende who perished in the coup 
witnesses said at four protesters suffered bullet wounds when 
pinochets bodyguards opened fire after the presidents motorcade 
was stoned in cerro navia a workingclass suburb north of santiato 
police did not report any injuries or arrests in cerro navia but 
said 142 people were arrested in vina del mar when militants tried 
to march from the cemetery into the city center 
pinochet the only candidate in next months presidential 
referendum was booed by hundreds of people when he arrived in 
cerro navia 
many hurled rocks at his motorcade according to radio 
cooperativa the broadcast said pinochets bodyguards fired shots 
into the air and vehicles in the motorcade drove around barricades 
of burning tires 
radio cooperativa said no one was seriously hurt but some people 
were hit by rocks and had minor injuries 
reporters at the scene said four people were struck by bullets 
and two manuel romero and orieta valvez were in serious condition 
with stomach wounds 
earlier sunday in a speech marking the sept 111973 overthrow 
of allende pinochet addressed an audience of 3000 people in a 
government office building among those present were pinochets 
fellow armed forces commanders and the 16member cabinet 
we will triumph in the upcoming challenge the 72yearold 
president said 
outside thousands of supporters rallied noisily on the street 
they waved red white and blue chilean flags and banners promoting 
a yes vote in the referendum 
an estimated 5000 people attended the memorial service for 
allende in vina del mar 75 northwest of santiago 
after the service thousands of leftists began a march from the 
suburban cemetery to the downtown area and were blocked by helmeted 
riot police fighting broke out about five blocks from the cemetery 
