not favor federal funding except in cases of rape incest or to 
save the mothers life but the national right to life committee 
and the national abortion rights action league both agree that 
bentsen has usually voted against restrictions on abortion funding 
and against constitutional amendments to ban abortion 
bentsen was absent july 27 when the senate voted 7319 to allow 
medicaid funding of abortions in promptly reported cases of rape or 
incest 
the house on a 216166 vote friday refused to go along with 
the senate move which would be the first liberalization of 
medicaid abortion funding in seven years the senate may take up 
the issue early this week 
bushs running mate sen dan quayle of indiana voted with that 
senate majority july 27 but naral says he was among many 
antichoice senators who voted for the amendment only as an 
alternative to accepting even fewer restrictions on medicaid 
funding 
quayle is rated highly by the antiabortion groups and lowly by 
naral quayle says he generally opposes abortion except to save the 
mothers life 
activists on both sides agree the next president is likely to 
make several appointments to the supreme court that could sway the 
tribunals ruling on abortion 
the current court has four justices who generally support the 
