<DOCNO> AP880912-0160 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
the environmental protection agency must focus 
on preventing pollution instead of concentrating on cleaning up 
existing problems with an end of pipe strategy a report 
provided monday recommended 
to help carry through such a change the agencys research 
budget should be increased by about 375 million a year roughly 
doubled said a committee of the agencys science advisory board 
in the report 
the study was made available by agency officials monday after an 
article about it appeared in the boston globe 
the committee was responding to a request for advice from epa 
administrator lee m thomas who the report said sensed that 
epas immediate regulatory needs were driving its research and 
development efforts while longerterm research equally important 
to achieving epas overall risk reduction goals was being 
neglected 
al alm former deputy administrator of epa and chairman of the 
highlevel advisory committee said in an interview that thomas was 
correct 
the problem epa has is its spending most of its rampd dollars 
just putting out legislative fires alm said referring to 
research and development money one of its major problems is to 
look ahead to anticipate problems 
obviously you need technical support for the regulations but 
that has driven virtually all the longterm research away he 
said 
the report said that in the 1970s efforts to control 
automobile industrial and wastewater pollution using federally 
mandated endofpipe controls were sensible targeted relatively 
efficient and reasonably cost effective 
though cleanups have been predicated on the notion that the 
polluter pays and those controls will still be important 
strategy must change the report argued 
for one thing we are discovering environmental contamination 
in our homes eg radon and in the statosphere eg 
chlorofluorocarbons that are not emitted by pipes in the 
traditional sense the report said 
for another thing endofpipe control has too often shifted 
pollution from one place to another for example from water to air 
for toxic pollutants removed from sewage streams by aeration 
techniques 
whenever possible environmental protection efforts first 
should be aimed at minimizing the amount of wastes or pollutants 
generated thus waste reduction at its source for example 
through product design changes industrial process changes or 
material substitution should be a primary objective the report 
said 
alm said he believed many businesses would welcome a vigorous 
program of technology transfer led by epa a program to show 
them how their processes could be changed to generate less waste 
the private sector has an incentive through liability 
questions alm said 
to help keep the need for longterm research in view epa should 
convert the position of assistant administrator for research and 
development from a presidential appointment to a career job the 
report argued 
in the 18 years for epas existence no one has held the job for 
more than three years and no leader has stayed at the agency 
long enough to implement a sustained longterm research 
strategy it said 
ecological research should get more emphasis having taken a 
back seat to research to support regulations aimed at protecting 
human health the report said 
</TEXT>
