hugh hefner founder chairman and chief 
executive officer of playboy enterprises announced monday he wont 
run for reelection to the companys board of directors and is 
passing full command to his daughter 
the company said in a statement that christie hefner is expected 
to be elected to the posts her father holds at a board meeting nov 
10 set to follow playboys 1988 shareholders meeting 
ms hefner 35 now is the companys president chief operating 
officer and vice chairwoman 
i think in terms of the company overall it is a changing of 
the guard a sort of passing the reins along said playboy 
spokeswoman robyn radomski in terms of where the company is now 
its a logical step but hef is still going to be 
editorinchief of the magazine and be involved in major strategic 
decisions 
once ms hefner becomes playboys top board executive the 
companys 62yearold founder will hold the titles of chairman 
emeritus and editorinchief of playboy magazine the company said 
christie has had my full support since she took responsibility 
for the daytoday operations of the company in april of 1982 
hefner said in a statement during this period she has directed 
a restructuring program that has resulted in an overall return to 
profitability 
this change is just another evolutionary step consistent with 
my own personal plans but i do not intend to reduce my commitment 
of time and effort to the success of the company said hefner 
who mortgaged his furniture and invested 600 to publish the first 
issue of playboy in december 1953 
hefner playboys major stockholder is working on his 
autobiography for which the company said it will receive a 
substantial sevenfigure advance from bantam books inc 
ms hefner said in a statement that she would help to continue 
to build the playboy franchise by expanding our licensing and 
television and video buinesses 
the geographic reach of the company also will continue to be 
expanded with new markets such as india and eastern bloc countries 
opening up for playboylicensed products and foreign distribution 
of home video and television programs growing she said 
under ms hefners leadership playboy enterprises closed the 
last of its us key clubs and shed its interests in movie 
theaters modeling and book and record clubs playboy enterprises 
made a 26 million profit in 1988 
dan lee an anaylst with drexel burnahm lambert inc in new 
york said hefner may have wanted to spend less time on business 
because of his plans to marry kimberley conrad 26 playmate of the 
month for january sometime next year hefner has been single since 
his divorce in 1952 
in a business sense christie hefner has largely been running 
the company for the past several years lee said but he owns 
about 80 percent of playboys stock so there wont be any dramatic 
changes 
