<TEXT>
margaret b mcfarland the child psychologist 
childrens television show host fred rogers described as the most 
major influence in my professional life died monday after a long 
illness she was 83 
highly regarded and recognized in the fields of child 
development education and psychology miss mcfarland cofounded 
the arsenal family and childrens center with dr benjamin spock 
and erik erikson in 1953 and served as its director until 1971 
she helped establish the department of child development and 
child care within the psychiatry department of university of 
pittsburghs school of medicine in the early 1950s 
she was so otherdirected that when you were in her presence 
you felt you were important said rogers host of mister 
rogers neighborhood the show is produced at wqedtv a 
pittsburgh public television station 
miss mcfarland earned masters and doctorate degrees at columbia 
university in 1928 and 1938 she was an associate professor of 
psychology in columbias psychiatry department from 1951 through 
1975 and became associate professor emeritus in 1976 the 
department is now part of the universitys school of social work 
she later became a consultant for rogers television show 
reviewing scripts and song lyrics 
</TEXT>
