<TEXT>
television sitcoms have always known about it presidential 
politicians have embraced it now the movies are redisovering the 
potent appeal of the family 
sweet hearts dance is the latest variation on the family 
theme and it is an unexpected winner no movie has so touched the 
heart since terms of endearment 
of course you might expect sweet hearts dance to be 
impressive when you note that the writer is ernest thompson his 
play and movie of on golden pond were exquisite depictions of 
the joys and sorrows of old age now he focuses on a younger 
generation of marrieds and abouttobe marrieds contributing an 
equal portion of humanity and understanding 
susan sarandon and don johnson have been married long enough for 
boredom to have set in she tolerates his macho pastimes he 
largely ignores her womanly longings he is a builder and their 
life in a norman rockwellian new england town is comfortable 
familiar and dull 
johnsons best buddy is jeff daniels he is a school principal 
a bit dull but by no means dumb a devout bachelor he is attracted 
to the new teacher in town elizabeth perkins but is wary of 
commitment 
the story is told in seasons each framed like an oldtime 
calendar the seasons change as do the relationships of the four 
characters 
johnson rankling under his loss of freedom finally moves out 
of the family house after a caribbean vacation with his lodge 
members the four lives are sorted out more or less 
a synopsis makes it seem that not much happens in sweet hearts 
dance but it is constantly engrossing tender without excess 
sentiment and often hilarious amazingly the film is the first 
feature directed by robert greenwald a television veteran who has 
a bright future in films 
thompsons script and greenwalds direction give the four stars 
equal opportunity to shine with her wise wondering eyes sarandon 
is the ideal portrayer of the 1980s woman johnson is a revelation 
displaying none of his miami vice schtick daniels is ideal for 
the role as the intelligent innocent and elizabeth perkins 
big registers again as a bright screen presence 
sweet hearts dance has so many moments to cherish that it 
should probably be seen twice for full appreciation 
the tristar release was produced by jeffrey lourie the rating 
is r mostly for language running time 101 minutes 
